COUNCIL ASKS PARENTS TO VACCINATE TODDLERS FOR FLU
----------------------------------------------------------------------

    Doctors and Richmond Council are urging local parents to vaccinate
    their toddlers against the flu this winter, after figures revealed
    that only 39.05% of 2-3 year olds in the borough received the free
    flu vaccination last year - a figure below national average
    of 43.5%.

